groups Webapp Example
==========================

  0. Begin in the auth-hello example directory and compile the example:

        $ cd $FABRIC/examples/groups
        $ ant

  1. Start the store. The 'start-all' script will start the
     store in a separate xterm window:

        $ bin/start-all

  2. Add default users alice and bob to the worker store:
  
        $ bin/init-state
  TODO: make this step unnecessary

  3. Start the web server:

        $ bin/start-webapp
  4. Use curl or similar client to interact with the groups REST-style API:
     - create a user:
        curl --cookie-jar cookies 'http://localhost:8080/groups/sif?action=adduser&user=owen&pass=password'
     - login a user:
        curl --cookie-jar cookies 'http://localhost:8080/groups/sif?action=login&user=owen&pass=password'
     - access pages requiring authentication
        curl -b cookies http://localhost:8080/groups/sif?action="frontPage"  
     - logoff
        curl -b cookies http://localhost:8080/groups/sif?action="frontPage"
  5. Exit the store with the "exit" command in its console (you can also
     use CTRL-D).

     You can clean up the store's persistent state by removing the 'var'
     directory:

        $ rm -rf var


References
----------
